				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>As a contact tracing app developer (<a href="http://covidsafepaths.org/" rel="nofollow ugc">http://covidsafepaths.org/</a>), I understand the criticism and concern. And I agree with most of it. </p>
<p>However, I also understand how new technologies and products get to the world, and how unpredictable the future is. I don&#8217;t think contact tracing is the solution to everything. But I also don&#8217;t take it out of this very complex equation. </p>
<p>Your post reads remarkably similar to Steve Ballmer&#8217;s &#8220;There&#8217;s no chance that the iPhone is going to get any significant market share. No chance&#8221;, in 2007. A very knowledgeable person, predicting something in his own field, using good scientific reason and extrapolations in existing data. </p>
<p>He just forgot to account for time. 😉</p>
