					<p>Interesting post.  South Korea is so often praised as a beacon of hope. In reality they are in virtually the same state of lockdown as every other country, thousands of businesses are closed without compensation because they had contact with an infected person, normal daily life is severely curtailed, yet they don&#8217;t even have the benefit of a significant minority of the population now being immune.</p>
