				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>No measure is perfect. Luckily they don&#8217;t have to be. With COVID19 you need to prevent around 2/3 of all infections to get lower numbers. </p>
<p>So a combination of hygiene, masks, contact tracing and some social distancing could be enough to keep R below 1. </p>
<p>This is quite different from the first few cases where not containing a single case can lead to exponential spread.</p>
